{
  "doc_id": "19471",
  "text": "There is little previous research that has addressed whether warm parenting teaches children about feelings independent of mother talk. One finding that bears an indirect relation is that securely attached children tend to do better on theory of mind/emotion tasks [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Secure attachment tends to be associated with a warmer and more open and communicative parenting style.",
